- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper analyzes the discourse on Twitter related to two protest hashtags.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper discusses the social implications of the protests and counter-protests.
- cs.SD (Software Development) is less likely but still possible as the paper may discuss the methodology used to analyze the Twitter data.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also less likely but possible as the paper may discuss the natural language processing techniques used to analyze the discourse.
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also possible as the paper analyzes the social behavior and attitudes reflected in the discourse on Twitter.
